The paper deals with graph layouts, which are a topic in both discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of a novel graph partition technique suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper's focus on the track and queue numbers of graphs suggests that it may also be relevant to the field of graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper's implications for 3D grid drawings suggest that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of computer science dealing with visualization and graphics (cs.SI).
